<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-437CF38A-538E-4CA8-9529-D3992775BBB1" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-437CF38A-538E-4CA8-9529-D3992775BBB1" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Clean the matrix plate area and the black protection cover</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-4890C8D2-E4F1-49EF-93EE-56CE06EFDF65"><p class="- topic/p ">The area around the matrix plate must be cleaned regularly. This includes the anti-reflective strips and mirror edges. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="d30323e12"><p class="- topic/p ">The operator panel gives a warning to perform this procedure at least once a month, and depending on the ink usage, between 7 and 30 days. 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p "> During the use of the printer, dust and fibers from the media can accumulate on the edges of the anti-reflective strips and mirrors of the printhead carriage. If these fibers touch the surface of the paper during printing, they can wipe through the uncured ink and can cause print quality issues. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> These print quality issues can easily be mistaken for printhead issues, as these fibers are stuck to the carriage. To prevent unnecessary service calls or printhead replacements, the edges of the anti-reflective strips and mirrors need to be cleaned regularly. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="d30323e19"><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-879FB967-1ACD-4EBB-8B95-AD7F42ACF7D5-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-879FB967-1ACD-4EBB-8B95-AD7F42ACF7D5-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Video: <ph class="- topic/ph " varid="Video: 5 - Clean the matrix plate"><xref class="- topic/xref " format="html" href="https://sus.cpp.canon/7T2BAH5G" scope="external"><?ditaot usertext?> 
<image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png"/> Clean the matrix plate</xref></ph> 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-223462BE-E8A6-42A4-8092-4911769DD50E" importance="recommended" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><p class="- topic/p ">Use <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> prescribed: 
</p><ul id="UL_88FE82F1C6B343028F9B61DB8C430ED7" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_F4B9AC154F1445FBAA8F889824E6FD43" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Microflex</ph> gloves for handling ink 
</p></li><li id="LI_6FA5A3A7E0FE4587B6D4539C231C8B45" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Swabs 
</p></li><li id="LI_E3654F6701EC4548A51C5EFFD5F5B599" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Cleaning liquid (Cleaner MB - methyl benzoate) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Cleaner IPA 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-153CC759-3960-41C2-B43D-821B59856AAF" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">For information on the prescribed maintenance materials. 
</p></note></prereq><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-9848D934-FF3E-4AC9-BA07-69028FA44036" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="SECTION_63E3642B0DFF489CBCD0BC953A812225" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><note id="GUID-B2E58ED3-A324-43BF-A7C4-DB5FD6B4C811" class="- topic/note " type="caution"><p class="- topic/p "> Wear gloves when contact with ink or maintenance materials is possible. Gloves should always overlap sleeves. Wear safety glasses with side shields when handling ink or maintenance materials. Follow the ink related Safety Data Sheets (SDS) guidelines carefully in order to ensure maximum safety. 
</p></note><note id="GUID-BF0C1923-1921-4C71-9F02-9D346E06E9D7" class="- topic/note " type="important"><p class="- topic/p "> Use the prescribed cleaning liquid. Do not use any other cleaners. 
</p></note></section><steps id="GUID-CBD6ADF1-6FC4-411E-A89A-E4C4292E3064" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="STEP_2DC73EFE13934A79ABD96C6989671B92" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Start the maintenance action via the operator panel. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_1616E37B85E54CEEBCD4115796DE06FF" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Put on the <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> approved gloves. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_93E05ACA63C543C2A891096692AF80A9" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Go to the media input side and locate the manual maintenance door on the left. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_A4A46D5F39D446D69F2FB5FD35EAE73B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FC882054-A59D-4AE0-8CB1-C4305AC9E512-low.png" id="IMAGE_9DBB3FC618A04C2D865668F2E289BA08" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FC882054-A59D-4AE0-8CB1-C4305AC9E512-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_5732956B832B443C9233D7DA0112A90F" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Open the media cover (1) and lift the lever of the manual maintenance door on the left (2). Close the cover before starting the maintenance to avoid bumping into it. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_2254A7BD56A744D785BE3BD4C4DB07CF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-688D946B-F927-42F9-BB8D-DF825978318D-low.png" id="IMAGE_66BAB896036D439DBE1A2041FF5EC4FB" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-688D946B-F927-42F9-BB8D-DF825978318D-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_612BA1CF3D804FDCA0F91F297D5FDB56" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Open the manual maintenance door (3). A light is switched on. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-253DB990-E2E4-4CCF-8B4F-9E610027C466" class="- topic/note " type="important"><p class="- topic/p ">Do not use any external light source to prevent curing of the ink and damage to the printheads. 
</p></note></info></step><step id="STEP_A7588866B6A041DA993C49AAEE2EF833" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Locate the matrix plate in the compartment. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_39B393E46CC9415FB0F33875F4594ACB" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Take a <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> approved swab. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Dampen the swab with cleaner MB and clean the dummy printheads, until all visible residue ink is gone. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">Depending on the printer configuration there are 3 or 4 dummy printheads. 
</p><fig id="GUID-A5794438-EE90-470F-9DC0-04B032ECC33A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6BAD91C7-7A4A-4046-B537-E40F8BDD56D9-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6BAD91C7-7A4A-4046-B537-E40F8BDD56D9-low.png"/></fig><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not touch the active printheads. When you touch them, you could damage the printheads. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Never put the swab between a printhead and the matrix plate area. 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-68A2ED10-DD53-4661-9731-84E735836460" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-456F8E28-62A5-40AD-B018-DD171F7E4548-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-456F8E28-62A5-40AD-B018-DD171F7E4548-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_814E5F6645D94775BFC1EB18257092A3" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Dampen a new swab with cleaner MB and clean the outer edge of the matrix plate until all visible residue ink is gone. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-D7ED9256-DF81-45C9-B120-2E40105B9087" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F39A76DC-4011-4426-9703-842C363E8CD7-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F39A76DC-4011-4426-9703-842C363E8CD7-low.png"/></fig></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-E9B073E1-F3E9-476C-B47C-D39564CB8C3F" class="- topic/note " type="important"><ul id="d448e87" class="- topic/ul "><li id="d448e88" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure to end the cleaning procedure within 5 minutes, when you use the cleaning liquid. The printer has to perform automatic maintenance after, to make sure the cleaning liquid does not damage the printheads. 
</p></li><li id="d448e91" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Use as many swabs as necessary. 
</p></li></ul></note></info></step><step id="STEP_5E80EE3FE112462BA9D53627BC68B011" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Locate the black protection cover and inspect if it is polluted with ink, media dust or fibers. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_5A7F4A380E444F3E9AFA164576B05AC6" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In case of pollution, take a new swab and clean the black protection cover especially the protruding parts (red indicated area). 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_C986DF1C644E45B29AF3DDF0DDB42AB1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6B59D35A-4689-46E8-B886-E2A680F44A88-low.png" id="IMAGE_8F2D51BA804F4DDDA2020384F24483B8" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6B59D35A-4689-46E8-B886-E2A680F44A88-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_98D7548DE66E403EACB0AD63C3B85466" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Only when necessary, dampen a new swab with the cleaner IPA and clean the polluted parts of the black protection cover again. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_76F0A63D8AB445668557A31E2651D569" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure that all residue ink is removed. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Use a lint free cloth with cleaner IPA to clean the edges of the left mirrors. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-9F4D1A66-AC40-4864-9861-36C869087B14" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3782BF1F-31C4-4492-A10A-A07F0EB8612A-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3782BF1F-31C4-4492-A10A-A07F0EB8612A-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Use a lint free cloth with cleaner IPA to clean the left black anti-reflective strip. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-0C221492-F6FB-4EEB-92B7-71D3D3B7B2A8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E2752D8A-0886-4B81-B1B1-514A260042E3-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E2752D8A-0886-4B81-B1B1-514A260042E3-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Use a lint free cloth with cleaner IPA to clean the edges of the right mirror and the right anti-reflective strip. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-F8580FD5-A422-43E8-91F1-3E514B845C54" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-81F48088-4255-43CE-9A2C-6A2DB3406614-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-81F48088-4255-43CE-9A2C-6A2DB3406614-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Dispose the gloves and swabs as chemical waste according to local regulations. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Close the manual maintenance door and the media cover. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note id="GUID-67F1D5EA-3940-42BB-AB48-88A1B2F79E34" class="- topic/note " type="important"><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure all covers are closed correctly to prevent cured ink in your system. 
</p></note></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> On the operator panel tap <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Completed</text></uicontrol></ph> to end the maintenance action. 
</cmd></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-412C614D-9E31-4E8D-B644-52D11B3C77FC.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>